resources:
/** Light variant of the legacy Material primary purple tone. */ #FFBB86FC
/** Primary variant of the legacy Material purple tone. */ #FF6200EE
/** Dark variant of the legacy Material primary purple tone. */ #FF3700B3
/** Light variant of the legacy Material secondary teal tone. */ #FF03DAC5
/** Dark variant of the legacy Material secondary teal tone. */ #FF018786
/** Pure black. Legacy Material baseline color. */ #FF000000
/** Pure white. Legacy Material baseline color. */ #FFFFFFFF
/** * Primary background color of the casino game table. * Represents the deep green felt surface of a craps or * blackjack table. All gameplay elements render on top * of this color. */ #1B5E20
/** * Surface color for UI panels, cards, and control areas * rendered above the table felt. Deep casino burgundy, * consistent with physical table rail and trim aesthetics. */ #5C2D1E
/** * Primary readable text color for content rendered * directly on the table felt surface. */ #F5F5F5
/** * Accent text color used for section headers and labels * that require visual distinction on the table surface. * Warm gold tone consistent with casino signage. */ #F5E9A8
/** * Text color for disabled UI elements such as inactive * buttons or unavailable actions. Rendered at reduced * visual prominence to communicate unavailability. */ #FF8A7A72
/** * Neutral base color of the dice face surface. * Represents the primary ivory/parchment tone of the die. */ #F2EBD3
/** * Light variation of the dice face for highlight areas. * Applied to regions simulating direct light exposure. */ #F7F3E3
/** * Dark variation of the dice face for shaded areas. * Applied to regions simulating ambient shadow on the die. */ #E6DEC2
/** * Highlight color applied to dice edges facing the light * source. Creates the illusion of a beveled, physical edge. */ #D8D2BE
/** * Shadow color applied to dice edges facing away from * the light source. Reinforces the three-dimensional * physical form of the die. */ #BFB8A3
/** * Background surface color rendered directly behind the dice * in the held state. Distinguishes the held dice area from * the surrounding table felt, providing spatial context for * the player's current hold selection. */ #5C2D1E
/** * Primary color used to render pip dots on all dice faces. * High-contrast black ensures maximum pip readability * against the ivory face surface at any screen size. */ #000000
/** * Background fill for action buttons in the disabled state. * Visually communicates that the action is currently * unavailable without removing the element from layout. */ #3D1E14
/** * Border color for action buttons in the disabled state. * Maintains button shape definition while reinforcing * the unavailable interaction state. */ #4A2419
